==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Saint-Simonian
<hw>Saint`-Si*mo"ni*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A follower
of the <person>Count de <etsep>St. Simon</etsep></person>, who died in
1825, and who maintained that the principle of property held in common,
and the just division of the fruits of common labor among the members of
society, are the true remedy for the social evils which exist.</def>
<rj><au>Brande & C.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Saint-Simonianism</ent>⟦br⟧
